  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to assess whether a SIMPLE or a COMPLEX strategy is best for the treatment of
      coronary bifurcation stenoses.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      500 patients will be randomised to either a SIMPLE strategy (provisional T stenting) or a
      COMPLEX strategy (crush or culotte stenting) with clinical follow-up at 9 months.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
